Requires that your iPhone and Mac are signed in with the same Apple Account using two‑factor authentication, your iPhone and Mac are near each other and have Bluetooth and Wi‑Fi turned on, and your Mac is not using AirPlay or Sidecar. Some iPhone features (e.g. camera and microphone) are not compatible with iPhone Mirroring.

  • Display: Screen size is measured diagonally. Actual diagonal screen size of the 24″ iMac is 59.69 cm (23.5″). The displays on MacBook Air with the M1 chip and the 13″ MacBook Pro measure 33.74 cm (13.3″) diagonally. The displays on the 13″ MacBook Air with M2 or M3, the 15″ MacBook Air, and the 14″ and 16″ MacBook Pro have rounded corners at the top. When measured as a standard rectangular shape, the screens are 34.46 cm (13.6″), 38.91 cm (15.3″), 35.97 cm (14.2″) and 41.05 cm (16.2″) diagonally (actual viewable area is less).
